Description: Collaborative academic word processor (bundled)
 Fidus Writer is an online collaborative editor especially made for academics
 who need to use citations and/or formulas. The editor focuses on the content
 rather than the layout, so that with the same text, you can later on publish
 it in multiple ways: On a website, as a printed book, or as an ebook.
 .
 Features:
  * Semantic word processing
  * Real-time collaboration
  * Citation management
  * Formula support with LaTeX
  * Multiple export formats (HTML, EPUB, LaTeX, DOCX)
  * Template system
  * Plugin architecture
 .
 This package includes Python compiled from source and all Python
 dependencies bundled in a virtualenv at /opt/fiduswriter/, making it
 self-contained and working on different versions of Ubuntu and Debian
 without requiring a modern system Python.
 .
 Node.js (>= 22) is required for JavaScript transpilation. On systems
 with a recent nodejs package, the system version is used. On older
 distributions, the companion fiduswriter-server-nodejs package is
 installed automatically to provide a bundled Node.js runtime.
 .
 This package includes all optional modules:
  * fiduswriter-books - Book document type support
  * fiduswriter-citation-api-import - Import citations from external APIs
  * fiduswriter-languagetool - Grammar and spell checking
  * fiduswriter-ojs - Open Journal Systems integration
  * fiduswriter-pandoc - Additional export formats via Pandoc
  * fiduswriter-phplist - PHPList newsletter integration
  * fiduswriter-gitrepo-export - Export to Git repositories
  * fiduswriter-payment-paddle - Paddle payment processing
  * fiduswriter-website - Static website generation

Package: fiduswriter-server-nodejs
Architecture: any
Depends: ${misc:Depends}
Description: Bundled Node.js runtime for Fidus Writer
 This package provides a bundled Node.js runtime (via nodejs-wheel)
 for Fidus Writer on systems where the distribution's Node.js package
 is too old (below version 22).
 .
 The main fiduswriter-server package prefers the system nodejs (>= 22)
 if available. This package is only installed automatically on older
 distributions that do not meet that requirement.
 .
 On systems with nodejs (>= 22) already installed, this package is
 not needed and will not be installed.
